{
  "stem": "19111.4",
  "chunk_idx": 5,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "In Kaunas, we thought that perhaps the furriers would be put back to work with furs.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But it turned out that they didn't need them anymore there.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Somehow the Kaunas Ghetto was also-- they knew that-- they had a knowledge of the liquidation of the Vilna Ghetto.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they lasted until 1944.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And we were there in the Kaunas Ghetto about two months or so.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And they started liquidating the Kaunas Ghetto.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I never, never learned why they did that.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was-- they probably wanted-- they had plans for Kailis.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they wanted to have a remnant of furriers just so that they would have something, because after we were taken away, Kailis was liquidated, including the other small camp, HKP.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "All the-- for the most [INAUDIBLE], except for those who were able to hide out or escape, were taken to Paneriai, and all were killed.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "After being incarcerated there for two and a half years, the finale was that they were all killed.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Most of them were killed in Paneriai.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, there was the one in charge-- see, I was so young, I couldn't remember the names.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "But they referred to him like [NON-ENGLISH], [NON-ENGLISH] meaning a-- a bear neck, because in the winter, he had a big, long neck.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so they gave him a nickname.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "They called him the [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that was the man who was in charge of the-- of the facility to-- the security of the camp.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Now, the head of the factories, they were civilian people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was an incident in the factory once where there was a man by the name of Oscar Gluck.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He was the one who was in charge, really, of the factory.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And there was a-- an-- a story what happened with him.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
